articles.description: Emmanuel Ndumanya scored a career-high 23 points, pulled down 10 rebounds and Josip Vrankic tossed in 19 points in Santa Clara's 81-72 win at Portland Thursday night.
articles.headline: Ndumanya scores 23 as Santa Clara holds off Portland 81-72

articles.description: Elijah Bryant scored nine of his 25 points in overtime and BYU held off upset-minded Pepperdine 75-70.
articles.headline: Bryant helps BYU holds off Pepperdine 75-70 in OT

articles.description: Michael Onyebalu had 24 points, Siler Schneider scored 16 and Rogers Printup added 15 points as UC Davis outlasted Cal Poly 92-84 in triple overtime on Thursday night.
articles.headline: UC Davis outlasts Cal Poly in triple overtime 92-84

articles.description: Brayon Blake had 24 points with 14 rebounds and Victor Sanders added 21 points as Idaho battled back late to beat Montana State 88-78 and win its fifth straight Big Sky Conference game Thursday night.
articles.headline: Idaho rallies to beat Montana State for 5th straight win

articles.description: Frankie Ferrari hits a 3 deep behind the arc to put San Francisco up 62-58 over Saint Mary's.
articles.headline: Clutch 3 extends San Francisco's lead

articles.description: Leland King II scored 20 points and grabbed 15 rebounds, Gabe Vincent added 19 points, and UC Santa Barbara pulled ahead early to beat Long Beach State 80-70 on Thursday night to remain atop the Big West Conference standings.
articles.headline: UC Santa Barbara beats Long Beach St 80-70
